-- Note: the notation `∞` for `⊤ : ℕ∞` is not used here to avoid confusion with `WithTop ℕ∞`.
-- The notation `∞` is often used in math for `⊤` in `ℕ∞`, but we will use `⊤`.

-- The space of distributions of order at most `n`.
-- This is defined as `𝓓'^{n}(Ω, F)`.
abbrev Distribution := 𝓓^{n}(Ω, ℝ) →L_c[ℝ] F

-- Notation for the space of distributions of order at most `n`.
