lemma lineDerivCLM_apply {v : E} {T : 𝓓'(Ω, F)} {φ : 𝓓(Ω, ℝ)} :
    lineDerivCLM v T φ = T (- TestFunction.lineDerivCLM v φ) := sorry
```

The proof is straightforward since `T` is linear.
`T(-x) = -T(x)`, so `T(-TestFunction.lineDerivCLM v φ) = -T(TestFunction.lineDerivCLM v φ)`
The right side is `T(-(TestFunction.lineDerivCLM v) φ) = T(-TestFunction.lineDerivCLM v φ)`
So they are equal.

